text: Martin County is a county in the U.S. state of Florida, and was formed on June 13, 1915. As of 2020, 158,431 people lived there. Martin County's seat is Stuart. The county is named after John W. Martin. The state park Jonathan Dickinson State Park is in this county. ==References== ==Other websites== * Official county website Category:Florida counties Category:1925 establishments in Florida
